OL,3,CHow Alderney could harness excess
OL,4,Ctidal power to mine Bitcoin
OL,6,FFounded in 2009 by an unknown person
OL,7,For group known as 'Satoshi Nakamoto',
OL,8,Fthe cryptocurrency is not reliant on
OL,9,Fany central authority and can be
OL,10,Ftraded between people online.
OL,12,FThe system doesn't rely on a bank for
OL,13,Fverification. Instead, a decentralised
OL,14,Fnetwork of computers confirms
OL,15,Ftransactions and records them in a
OL,16,Fpublic ledger called 'the blockchain'.
OL,18,FIt makes each Bitcoin unique,
OL,19,Fpreventing people from copying and
OL,20,Fspending the same one multiple times.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G3/15
