OL,3,CHow Alderney could harness excess
OL,4,Ctidal power to mine Bitcoin
OL,6,FSome argue it is more secure than
OL,7,Fphysical assets, as it is not
OL,8,Fregulated by countries or states.
OL,10,FThe cryptocurrency has become more
OL,11,Faccessible in recent years, partly due
OL,12,Fto its skyrocketing value. Nine years
OL,13,Fago, one bitcoin was worth roughly
OL,14,F#550. Now it is worth around #80,000.
OL,16,FWhy is it called 'Bitcoin mining'?
OL,18,FUnlike cash in your wallet, Bitcoin
OL,19,Fonly exists in the digital world.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G4/15
