OL,3,CHow Alderney could harness excess
OL,4,Ctidal power to mine Bitcoin
OL,6,F"I wouldn't want it to have any impact
OL,7,Fon any other services that the States
OL,8,Fhave already provided."
OL,10,FThe problems
OL,12,FWith the sheer amount of power that
OL,13,Fcrypto mining demands, not everyone is
OL,14,Fconvinced Alderney has the
OL,15,Finfrastructure to cope.
OL,17,FCrypto mining and data centres account
OL,18,Ffor 2% of global electricity,
OL,19,Faccording to the International
OL,20,FMonetary Fund in 2024.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws        G12/15
